.TH "devm_reset_controller_register" 9 "devm_reset_controller_register" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_reset_controller_register \- resource managed reset_controller_register()
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" devm_reset_controller_register
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct reset_controller_dev *rcdev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device that is registering this reset controller
.IP "rcdev" 12
a pointer to the initialized reset controller device
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Managed \fBreset_controller_register\fP. For reset controllers registered by
this function, \fBreset_controller_unregister\fP is automatically called on
driver detach. See \fBreset_controller_register\fP for more information.
